crs_scope: Geodetic survey.
remarks: Extended from Japan to Korea in 1898. In Japan, replaced by Tokyo 1918 (CRS code 4301). In South Korea replaced by Tokyo 1918 only for geodetic applications; for all other purposes replaced by Korean 1985 (code 4162).
information_source: Clifford J. Mugnier; in Photogrammetric Engineering & Remote Sensing November 1999. http://www.asprs.org

crs_scope: Large and medium scale topographic mapping, cadastral and engineering survey.
remarks: Replaces Tokyo 1892 / Korea East Sea Belt (CRS code 5172). Although it was intended that the grids were for most practical purposes coincident a 10.405" (250m) longitude offset was introduced. Replaced by Korean 1985 / Modified East Sea Belt (code 5177).

crs_scope: Large and medium scale topographic mapping, cadastral and engineering survey.
remarks: Introduced to replace Korean 1985 / Central Belt (CRS code 2097) on Jeju to avoid negative northing coordinates. Replaced by Korean 1985 / Modified Central Belt Jeju (code 5175).

crs_scope: Large and medium scale topographic mapping, cadastral and engineering survey.
remarks: Sometimes incorrectly assumed to be Tokyo 1918 / Korea West Belt, a system that was never put into use. In South Korea, replaced by Korean 1985 / West Belt (CRS code 2098).
information_source: Clifford J. Mugnier; in Photogrammetric Engineering & Remote Sensing November 1999. http://www.asprs.org

crs_scope: Large and medium scale topographic mapping, cadastral and engineering survey.
remarks: Sometimes incorrectly assumed to be Tokyo 1918 / Korea Central Belt, a system that was never put into use. In South Korea, replaced by Korean 1985 / Central Belt and Korean 1985 / Central Belt Jeju (CRS codes 2097 and 5168).
information_source: Clifford J. Mugnier; in Photogrammetric Engineering & Remote Sensing November 1999. http://www.asprs.org

crs_scope: Large and medium scale topographic mapping, cadastral and engineering survey.

crs_scope: Large and medium scale topographic mapping, cadastral and engineering survey.

crs_scope: Large and medium scale topographic mapping, cadastral and engineering survey.
remarks: Unofficial system replacing Korean 1985 / West Belt (code 2098) to correct 10.405" longitude difference and make grid for most practical purposes coincident with Tokyo 1892 / West Belt (code 5169). Replaced by Korea 2000 / West Belt (code 5180).
information_source: Korean Association of Surveying and Mapping.

crs_scope: Large and medium scale topographic mapping, cadastral and engineering survey.
